1 First of all, install git if you don't have it yet, and create a GitHub account. ( You can refer to the lesson "Install Git and Create GitHub Account" in the prework. Follow the guidelines given there. Additionally, you can use these resources: Install git, Version control with git)

Solution:
Install git!

2 Create a new repository in the GitHub. Name it Iron+ your name. Example: if your name is Alvaro, you will name the repo IronAlvaro.

Solution:
IronSebastiaan

3 Clone that repo to your computer.

Solution:
git clone https://github.com/Sebastiaan-K/IronSebastiaan.git

4 Create a file in that folder. Name it about.txt and add a fun fact about yourself. (You can use the command line: touch nameOfTheFile.txt).

Solution:
touch funfact.txt
echo "I LOVE GIT" > funfact.txt

5 Add the file you just created to the git.

Solution:
git add --all

6 Commit the changes.

Solution:
git commit -m "first commit"

7 Push the changes to the GitHub and check your repository to make sure everything is there.

Solution:
git push origin master

Pair Programming Exercise
Pair yourself with a classmate. Send the link of your GitHub repository to your pair via Slack. Now each of you should perform the following set of actions:

8 Fork your classmate's repository.

Solution:
Fork in git!

9 Clone the repository, so that you have it locally and can make changes.

Solution:
cd Ironhack
git clone https://github.com/Sebastiaan-K/IronPaul.git

10 Create a new branch named classmate.

Solution:
git branch clasmate


11 Create a new file with your name (ex. maya.txt) and finish the following sentence I enrolled Ironhack's Data Analytics bootcamp because.... When you are done, save the changes.

Solution:
I enrolled Ironhack's Data Analytics bootcamp because i want to become a data analyst! Sebastiaan.txt

12 Add the changes to the git.

Solution:
git add -A

13 Commit and push the changes. Now, all the changes should be on your GitHub, inside the forked repository.

Solution:
git commit -m "Added Sebastiaan.TXT"
git push

14 Create a pull request to make changes appear in the original repository.

Solution:
Send pull request on github

15 Merge the branch your classmate created. Now everyone's repos should have the original file (about.txt) as well as the new one with your classmate's name.

Solution:
Merge on github

